<H1><SAMP>umask</SAMP>: Tip</H1>


<P>To make changes to the default access permissions
which last until you next change them, place the umask
command in your login file.</P>

<P>Which file this is depends upon the shell that you use:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80><STRONG>Shell               login file</STRONG>
<HR>
Bourne shell	    .profile
Korn shell	    .profile
BASH		    .profile
C shell		    .login
TC shell	    .login
</PRE>

